article.description: Southern takes down Mississippi Valley State 17-7
article.headline: Southern takes down Mississippi Valley State 17-7
article.linkText: Southern takes down Mississippi Valley State 17-7
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. -- Dray Joseph had 288 yards passing and a touchdown as Southern scored two fourth-quarter touchdowns to take down Mississippi Valley State 17-7 in a Southwestern Athletic Conference game Saturday night. A 22-yard field goal by Southern's Greg Pittman in the first half was the only score until the fourth quarter as both teams struggled on offense. Southern (2-2, 2-0 SWAC) earned its second conference victory with the win over the Delta Devils (0-4, 0-2 SWAC). Lenard Tillery's 5-yard touchdown run early in the fourth quarter broke the scoring drought to put Southern up 10-0. Joseph later connected with Lee Doss for a 60-yard touchdown reception with 8:04 left to give the Jaguars a 17-0 lead. Doss caught a game-high 10 passes for 164 yards to lead the Jaguars. Patrick Ivy found the end zone on a 3-yard run with less than a minute remaining for Mississippi Valley State.
